<br>
This is my 7th mmorpg, and the the most fun I've had with one since EQ 4+ yrs ago, and I'm not a fanboi.  Really, I had no intention of buying this game.  I finally caved because of word of mouth on this board.  The csr's DO enforce the naming policy.  Of the four times I've sent in to customer service, I got responses back immediately.  I know everyone isn't having that experience, but its a helluvalot better than the service I get from Sony.  In fact, my customer service from Sony while on SW:G was the absolute worse of any game I have ever played.  I only came back to FV for the community, as I've stated several times on other threads.<br>
<br>
The community building on Dawn is wonderful.  I have yet to hear l33t $p33k, and have only heard a shout with abbreviation once.  If you aren't getting enough rp, then stop running around and rp with someone instead of just running past everyone.  Hell, I get rp'ed responses from people over my emotes.  <br>
<br>
I've played one mmorpg after another since EQ, and they were disappointments for me, one after another, until Horizons.   <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/danykalla/danyxa.html"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://pic3.picturetrail.com/VOL18/605666/2739889/39298091.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Art by Dorian Cleavenger</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zekspawn>Zekspawn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/22/03 1:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2241.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Horizons</span><hr size=1> The funny thing is, is that for the first week and a half, I had the same standpoint as you folks.  &quot;Just wait a bit, they'll fix it.&quot;  But mining ore and chopping wood can only take your amusement so far.  I just woke up one morning and thought to myself...you know what?  I'm not going to give these guys 12.95 a month..I already blew 50 on em.  NO bugs have been fixed and from what I understand...the game is in at least the same state as it was in the middle of beta testing.  <br>
<br>
The company realeased an unfinnished product and my free month was spent more waiting for servers to come up/waiting for NPCs to load than it was exping.<br>
<br>
I can almost promise that most of you will abandon this game in a few months because I really don't see it progressing.  I honestly believe it will go the way of Asheron's Call 2 and wait for someone to buy it out to keep it running for the 3 thousand loyal folk.  <br>
<br>
When they balance Elemental Archers so Ice arrow doesn't work as well, people will gripe, complain and quit.  They had many months of beta to get this right and the once broken classes (reavers and elemental archers) are overpowered and the once overpowered classes (dragons) are pretty much a joke.   My wife's dragon was several levels higher than I was (she wanted to keep her crafting level equal to her adventure rating) and my Spiritist was soloing mobs higher than she was killing.<br>
<br>
On the Spirit server (the newest roleplay server), there was a guild called &quot;Fourth Reich&quot;...which, by the way is the name of a Nazi movement in America.  I reported it, as did my wife and the guild tag was still there 5 days later.  There was a guy named &quot;Wha Tifaq&quot; (sound it out) he was reported and was still around a week later.  Someone wanted to ask me a question..he started it with &quot;Yo...blah blah blah&quot; to which I responded, in a roleplaying manner.  I was a fiend and he was a fiend, after all...we didn't need to use commoner jibberish.  He called me anal and got into a rules discussion with me and then tried to say that I was harrassing him.<br>
<br>
The game is a joke...there are zombies the whole way up...not because it's themed that you're supposed to be fighting undead, but because they didn't want to make new models.  Same goes for skeletons, ghosts and spiders.  <br>
<br>
I went exploring near Kirasanct and saw the same mobs that you see near Tazoon, and the other tropical areas...except the creatures were blue instead of orange &gt;&lt; and the skeletons had tails and horns.  That's the only difference and I've explored enough to see the level 30-40 mobs.<br>
<br>
Again, I'm glad you have a great community on your server..but that's becasue of the people and not the game.  When you're level 15, take a gander at what you're killing...maggots and zombies and skeletons and beetles.  Just like you were fighting at level 2 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   OK, well maybe you've moved onto one of the 80000 golems in the game (sandstone) or maybe you went onto pigmies (I liked the pigmies <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  they don't look like a wolf, spider or skeleton!)  The graphics, etc are not worth the extra stuff you need to run the game.  You need bigger specs on your comp not because of the higher graphics, but because they are streaming the information to your hard drive.  This brings me to an other thing.  <br>
<br>
Right click on start, explore, find Artifact entertainment, and look for your log files.  OH, you didn't turn on your log files?  To bad, they are on by default and everytime you log off, it stores another 4 files onto your hard drive.  Make sure you keep that clean or your comp will proceed to become slower and slower and slower.  You can't turn off the logs, unless you do it in the explore, AE thing.  I would love to tell you exactly how to do it, but, sadly, I deleted the game.  You'll have to find em yourself.  <br>
<br>
OH and if you want to level some of your lower level stuff...there is a cat woman near where you port into Kion.  Talk to her.  She'll give you quests that raise both your crafting and your adventure rating.  Two of em are deliver this note quest which give 200 in each the first time and 100 in each for the rest of the time, of of em is kill 10 beetles for, I think, the same reward.  The good one, though is 10 zombie fingers, where you get 500 in each school the first time.  <br>
<br>
The gems you find for socketing...consume em..yet an other way to get exp *nods*<br>
<br>
*shrug* The swimming through the ground thing lasts for quite a long time.  When I logged on the one time, I fell through the world and got recalled to my bind point.  No one in the game can swim <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  but you can't drown.  You just get recalled to your bind point when you are on land to long.  So if you want to explore areas on the other side of water, equip a floating cargo disk, because you can not recall with a cargo disk on.  This is the only way to access some areas of the game, so I recommend you get a cargo disk or start bugging folk to make masons to make you a bridge.  Masons have no real money making potential, because they can only build houses and the like &gt;&lt;  so, you'll have a hard time finding them as well.<br>
<br>
Once again, I'm glad you all like the game so much...I liked it when I first got it too...just to much trouble and I refuse to pay to beta test <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thilda>Thilda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/22/03 1:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2241.topic&index=16>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Horizons</span><hr size=1> Actually, the only real frustration I've experienced is the way SO MANY people want to RP. Kind of an odd problem, eh? But I'll find myself sneaking in an hour to explore, and I end up spending half of it RPing. On Dawn, all you have to do is slow your steps around someone, I've found, and people will start to RP with you. Maybe it has something to do with being one of the only bearded Dwarf women I've seen, but I've found most people are looking for, and initiating RP. They'll also drop a hunt and just head off into the wilderness to explore at the drop of a hat. Lots of fun.<br>
<br>
The only downside to being a scarce commodity (a dwarf woman) is that nearly every dwarven male I've come across is starved for female companionship. Poor fellows. My name's not Stoneheart for nothin' !<br>
<br>
Yes, you see the same types of mobs (the living are being beseiged by the undead, so that's not surprising). But did you take the time to find out the stories behind the different places? The strawblights and skeletons south of Dalimond are haunting the blasted site of a destroyed village that you have to scout out for a quest, for example. That bunch of skeletons you passed on the road a while back might have been the remnants of a dwarven patrol lost when it was swallowed in the rising tide of undead. <br>
<br>
They've done a very good job of making the countryside a real place that was populated by people with a history. It's fairly empty now, but the tattered remnants of the living population have been forced to retreat into a few towns. It's OUR job to repopulate the countryside and rebuild the fallen bridges and walls. That's part of the game, and one of the strengths of the community. <p>Thilda Stoneheart<br>
Wielder o' th' Beardbraids<br>
Dwarven armorer 'n scout<br>
